# Component Architecture

## Core Approach

- Functional components with TypeScript interfaces
- Ant Design components with consistent patterns
- Proper loading states and error handling
- Smart status detection for processing states

## Reference Implementations

- **Table Component**: `src/components/DataTable.tsx`

  - Column definitions
  - Status rendering with ProcessingProgress
  - Action buttons based on completion state

- **Processing Component**: `src/components/ProcessingProgress.tsx`

  - Smart completion detection
  - Status visualization (spinner, complete, error)
  - Consistent progress representation

- **Form Component**: `src/components/Upload/UploadModal.tsx`

  - Form validation
  - File upload integration
  - Loading states

- **Modal Component**: `src/components/PublicationModal.tsx`

  - Complex form handling
  - External API integration
  - Input sanitization patterns

- **List Component**: `src/components/DataList.tsx`
  - Item rendering
  - Hover states
  - Filter integration

## Key Patterns

- Component prop interfaces from DataTable.tsx
- Form handling from UploadModal.tsx
- Loading/error states from any page component
- Ant Design integration patterns throughout components/
- Processing status logic from ProcessingProgress.tsx

## Processing Status Patterns

### Status Display Component

```typescript
// Use centralized processing logic
import { calculateProcessingProgress } from '../utils/processingSteps';

const StatusComponent = ({ dataset }) => {
  const progress = calculateProcessingProgress(dataset);

  if (dataset.has_error) {
    return <Tag color="error">Error</Tag>;
  }

  if (progress.isComplete) {
    return <Tag color="success">Complete</Tag>;
  }

  return <ProcessingProgress dataset={dataset} />;
};
```

### Smart Status Detection

- Handle "no results found" cases where processing completed but flags show incomplete
- Use fallback logic: all prior steps done + idle status + no errors = completed
- Distinguish between "processing incomplete" vs "processing complete but no results"

### Action Button States

```typescript
// Enable actions based on actual completion status
const isComplete = calculateProcessingProgress(dataset).isComplete;

<Button
  disabled={!isComplete}
  type={isComplete ? "primary" : "default"}
>
  {isComplete ? "Publish" : "Processing..."}
</Button>
```

## Input Handling Patterns

- **Flexible Input Acceptance**: Accept multiple input formats (URLs, IDs, etc.)
- **Input Sanitization**: Use regex patterns to extract essential data from various formats
- **Pre-validation**: Validate input format before external API calls
- **User Guidance**: Update placeholder text to indicate acceptable formats

